cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper deals with semantic segmentation of remote sensing data using convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an incremental learning methodology, which involves adapting the network to learn new as well as old classes on the new training data, and allowing it to remember the previously learned information for the old classes. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques for balancing the discrepancy between outputs for the previous classes from the memory and updated networks, and the mis-classification rate between outputs for the new classes from the updated network and the new ground-truth. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
